16/03/2007
FRANKFURT, Germany -- After four years on the run, Andrija Draskovic, described as the successor of late Serbian gang leader Zeljko Raznatovic Arkan -- was arrested at Frankfurt's airport on Thursday (March 15th). 
He had arrived on a flight from Belgrade and was apprehended based on an international warrant issued by the Bari anti-mafia department. 
Italian authorities describe him as "one of the most important mafia bosses in the former Yugoslavia". 
He faces charges of drug and cigarette smuggling in Italy. 
(B92, Tanjug, RTRS, Ansa - 16/03/07)
